<body>
    <h1>FC05: Oracle EPM Cloud</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <ul>
<li>
<p>SailPoint IIQ solution shall have the ability to connect with four Oracl=
e EPM Cloud modules using connectors as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Planning (EPBCS) using out of the box Oracle Cloud EPM Cloud Connector</=
p></li>
<li>
<p>Financial Consolidation and Close (FCCS) using out of the box Oracle Clo=
ud EPM Cloud Connector</p></li>
<li>
<p>Account Reconciliation (ARCS) using out of the box Oracle Cloud EPM Clou=
d Connector</p></li>
<li>
<p>Oracle Enterprise Data Management Cloud Service (EDMCS) using Webservice=
 connector.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>SailPoint IIQ solution shall be able to create and manage user accounts =
in Oracle EPM Cloud.</p></li>
<li>
<p>SailPoint IIQ solution shall be able to perform user groups provisioning=
 and de-provisioning in Oracle Cloud EPM Cloud.</p></li>
<li>
<p>SailPoint IIQ solution will support the approval process for manually re=
quested access to prevent unauthorized access.</p></li>
<li>
<p>SailPoint IIQ solution shall have the ability to evaluate Segregation Of=
 Duties (SOD) conflicts when a user request is submitted to prevent SOD con=
flicts.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Please refer to section 11 use cases mentioned below for user account li=
fecycle management.</p></li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p><strong>Dependency:</strong></p>
<p>Table-11</p>
